<p>To-do list applications are perfect for realizing the potential of an uncharted language or framework. One reason I made <%= link_to "Magenda", "http://magenda.co" %> was to find out what Angular could do. You could call this a modern-day "<%= link_to "Hello World", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%22Hello,_World!%22_program" %>". Below you'll see the design and develop process.</p>

<h2>Requirements</h2>
<p>The application needed to be browser-based, but I had no other specs. Thus, I needed to determine the other requirements. A few things came to mind.</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Allow users to create as many to-do items as they wish.</li>
		<li>Allow users to delete items.</li>
		<li>Allow users to mark items as complete.</li>
		<li>Don't use a database.</li>
		<li>Build it in an unfamilar framework – <em>(Angular was new to me)</em>.</li>
</ul>

